BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1930853105
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:CANCELLED! Friday Biweekly Brewpub / Lunch Ride (Ron Fleischer)
DESCRIPTION:Status: CANCELLED!\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 25-35 miles\n
 \nLeader: Ron Fleischer\n\n!Elmhurst%20Windmill%202017.jpg: https://ebcrid
 es.org/images/cal/BrewPubBikeTour.jpgInterested in combining light exercis
 e and consumption of adult beverages on Friday afternoons? We will visit b
 reweries\, brewpubs\, and one distillery this summer to partake in craft b
 eer\, cider and other fine beverages (yes\, teetotalers are welcome). Each
  ride will partner adult beverages with lunch\, however some of our chosen
  locations are not brewpubs\; for those visits\, we will stop at a nearby 
 restaurant for lunch. About 25 - 35 miles.\n\nAs posted in advance on the 
 Rides Forum\, we will be visiting the following brewpubs that serve food t
 his year: Une Annee\, Eris Brewery and Cider House\, Steep Ravine (nee Rav
 inia) in Highland Park\, Bungalow by Middle Brow\, Half Acre\, Old Irving 
 Brewing Co.\, and Pho No1 Brewing. For cocktail fans\, we’ll visit the K
 oval Distillery Tasting Room.\n\nWe will make two other trips to visit bre
 weries on Malt Row without food service\, like Hop Butcher to the World\, 
 Dovetail\, Begyle and Is/Was. For those\, we’ll get local pizza\, burger
 s or sandwiches on the way. Rides begin May 16\, and occur every other Fri
 day.\n\nRide Leader: Ron Fleischer rfleisch1@yahoo.com\n\n
LOCATION:Chandler-Newberger Center\, Evanston\, IL
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
