UID:TU1941588473
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Ride to Lincoln Park from Chandler (Cynthia Karabush)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Casual\n\nDistance: 20 miles\n\nLead
 er: Cynthia Karabush\n\nRenovations of the Alfred Caldwell Lily Pool (a Na
 tional Historic Landmark) have finally been finished\, so we'll take the L
 akefront Trail south to Lincoln Park and visit this lovely pool. Where to 
 stop for food? Choices are endless in Lincoln Park\, but it's congested an
 d I'd rather leave before lunch traffic builds. There's a Marianos on the 
 way back if we want to be quick\, or if we feel like a nice sit-down Liban
 ais is nearer the end of our ride north on the North Shore Channel Trail -
  we can decide then.\n\ninformation on the man and the pool of the same na
 me: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred\\_Caldwell: https://en.wikipedia.
 org/wiki/Alfred_Caldwell\n\n
LOCATION:Chandler Park\, Evanston
CATEGORIES:..Casual (10-12 mph),.Weekly > ...Casual Wkly
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
