BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1954825107
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Western Suburbs Meander\, Fall Edition (Rebecca Tung)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 46 miles\n\nLe
 ader: Rebecca Tung\n\n# !https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Southern%20Caf%C3
 %A9.jpg\n\n# !https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Madison%20Meadow%20Lombard.j
 pg\n\n## Western Suburbs Meander\, Fall Edition\n\nRemote start at Madison
  Meadows Park in Lombard at 9AM\, Madison St entrance (Madison &amp\; Chas
 e). We’ll ride at a moderate pace (13-15mph)\, going through Lombard\, G
 len Ellyn\, Wheaton\, Winfield\, West Chicago\, Barlett\, Wayne to St Char
 les. Lunch at Southern Cafe in St Charles and going back the same way with
  minor variations.\n\nThe total riding distance will be 46 miles\, all on-
 road with some moderately challenging hills. We’ll wait to regroup after
  the climbs and no one will be left behind. Madison Meadows Park is about 
 70 min from Evanston by car\, it’s approximately 2 miles away from the M
 etra station in Lombard. Click this link for exact location https://maps.a
 pp.goo.gl/t6yM2E58HeLYza4Y6\n\n
LOCATION:Madison Meadow Park\, E Madison St & S Ahrens Ave\, Lombard\, IL 6
 0148
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20251011T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20251011T090000
CREATED:20250919T025146Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260112T230621Z
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/ks4f2ityp82zqj3zsh/events/1954825107
X-TEAMUP-STATUS:Confirmed
X-TEAMUP-PACE:Moderate
X-TEAMUP-DISTANCE:46 miles
X-TEAMUP-START-LOCATION:Madison Meadow Park\, E Madison St & S Ahrens Ave\,
  Lombard\, IL 60148
X-TEAMUP-LEADER:Rebecca Tung
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1964507232
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY: (Randy Pickard)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Fast Plus\n\nDistance: 48 miles\n\nL
 eader: Randy Pickard\n\nRemote start Fast Plus (17-19 mph) ride. The Plank
  Road Trail is the paved Illinois section of the Great_American_Rail_Trail
 : https://www.railstotrails.org/greatamericanrailtrail/ (the ambitious eff
 ort to create a cross country bike trail by 2040). We'll ride from Jurgens
 en Woods to the east side of Joliet and back. A highlight of the ride is t
 he Octoberfest Festival in Frankfort IL. The trail forms the northern boun
 dary of the festival grounds.\n\nWe'll start at 9:00 am from the eastern a
 ccess point to the trail at Forest Preserve Parking Lot\, IL-83\, Chicago 
 Heights\, IL 60411. (Jurgensen Woods)\n\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/place
 /Forest+Preserve+Parking+Lot/@41.5457423\,-87.5643648\,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4
 m5!3m4!1s0x880e1f60962c86dd:0xb00c476d45953cc!8m2!3d41.5457383!4d-87.56217
 61\n\nWe'll stop for lunch in Frankfort. The quaint town of Frankfort is e
 ssentially the midpoint of the trail\, so when we get there on the return 
 trip to Jurgensen Park we will have done about 48 miles of riding. Thus\, 
 bring pocket food for a quick mid ride stop on the outskirts of the Joliet
  Prison (made famous by the Blues Brothers).\n\nThe Octoberfest festival o
 ffers lots of outdoor dining options as we pass through Frankfort on the r
 eturn leg of the ride.\n\nPlease let Randy know via email if you are inter
 ested in joining the ride: randy.pickard@gmail.com\n\n**The Route - RideWi
 thGPS:** https://ridewithgps.com/routes/37192562\n\n
LOCATION:North Creek Meadow Forest Preserve Parking Lot\, IL-83\, Chicago H
 eights\, IL 60411
CATEGORIES:.Fast Plus (17-19 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20251011T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20251011T090000
CREATED:20251005T022247Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260112T230622Z
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/ks4f2ityp82zqj3zsh/events/1964507232
X-TEAMUP-STATUS:Confirmed
X-TEAMUP-PACE:Fast Plus
X-TEAMUP-DISTANCE:48 miles
X-TEAMUP-START-LOCATION:North Creek Meadow Forest Preserve Parking Lot\, IL
 -83\, Chicago Heights\, IL 60411
X-TEAMUP-LEADER:Randy Pickard
END:VEVENT
