BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2028940471
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Club Meeting: Three Months Biking the TransAmerica Trail (Anne Glas
 er)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nLeader: Anne Glaser\n\n## Club meeting: Re
 freshments at 7pm\, program begins at 7:30pm\n\n# **Biking the TransAmeric
 a Trail \n\nIn late August of last year\, club members Noreen Edwards and 
 Mark Metz started their trek on the TransAmerica Trail by dipping the rear
  tires of their recumbent bikes into the Pacific Ocean. Ninety-two days an
 d 4\,116 miles later\, they ended their self-supported journey in Yorktown
 \, VA. It was a bike-trip of a lifetime for a worthy cause – to raise mo
 ney to remodel the men’s residence at McGaw YMCA. (McGaw is still accept
 ing donations at https://www.mcgawymca.org/miles-that-matter.)\n\nCome to 
 the March meeting (the last one at the Robert Crown Center) to hear their 
 tales of biking across this country with a whiney hub and a squeaky seat. 
 They will be bringing their bikes for people to examine\, a Bacchetta Bell
 a Pronto for Noreen and a titanium Carver Ti-Glide for Mark.\n\nThe in-per
 son meeting at the Robert Crown Center (1801 Main St\, Evanston) will begi
 n at 7:30 pm with club business immediately followed by the pro-gram. We
 ’ll be upstairs in the Stein Room (Room D). Refreshments will be availab
 le starting at 7 pm.\n\n!https://files.teamup.com/7360314/attachment/01KJT
 DVWSCWK0WB9P2SYA9QCVW/preview/image.png?hash=b4742bae49304cf47bcc375a4b3d7
 1774fac6d7767445420c1fdf758818d54ac\n\n
LOCATION:Robert Crown Center\, Evanston
CATEGORIES:_Meetings/Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
