BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2051901701
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Arlington 500 Ride ($) (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Any\n\nDistance: 41 Miles\n
 \nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/AHBC%20Ar
 lington%205000.jpgThe Arlington 500 is a recreational bike ride on scenic 
 roads in Lake County\, Illinois. The Arlington Heights Bicycle Club (AHBC)
  has hosted this ride for over 40 years. This ride is similar to the NSC i
 n that riders can choose their  \nown pace and distance of a 20\, 41\, 66\
 , 87\, or 101 mile route. RWGPS  \nroutes and print cue sheets can be down
 loaded. There will also be  \nsignage road markers.\n\nRest stop with wide
  variety of food and beverages until 3:00PM.  \nSupport vehicles on the ro
 ute until 3:30PM.  \nMostly level terrain with some moderate hills.\n\nWe 
 will meet as a group beforehand and self-sort into pace and distance group
 s.\n\n**Start: Lake Zurich High School\, 300 Church Street\, Lake Zurich\,
  IL 60047.**\n\nDetails and sign-up are available on the Arlington Heights
  Bicycle Club website:\n\nhttps://cyclearlington.com/AHBC-500/Arlington-50
 0.html\n\nRWGPS routes can be found at  \nhttps://cyclearlington.com/AHBC-
 500/Arlington-500-Route.html\n\nNote that the routes (A through E) are add
 itive (i.e.\, all start and end at the starting location). To ride your de
 sired distance\, you will download multiple loops building up to your desi
 red ride.\n\n**Please RSVP Ride Leader if you are planning to ride.**\n\n
LOCATION:Lake Zurich High School\, 300 Church Street\, Lake Zurich\, IL 600
 47
CATEGORIES:...Any
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
