BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2057358189
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Burlington\, WI (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Fast Plus\n\nDistance: 56 M
 iles\n\nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWG
 PS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/40014510\n\n!https://ebcrides
 .org/images/cal/WisconsinBiking.jpgThis ride will be on quiet rural roads 
 with little traffic and some steep hilly sections\, but mostly rollers. Th
 is ride is surprisinglyscenic given it's only about an hour's drive from E
 vanston. There will be a lunch stop at the Coffee Shop in Burlington\, and
  short break at miles 20 and 45. if you plan on coming along on the ride o
 r have any question please email Jay Twery @ jaytwery@gmail.com\n\nIf the 
 weather doesn't cooperate Jay will post a cancellation on the Rides Forum 
 by 7:30 on the day of the ride.\n\n**Directions to the start:**\n\nhttps:/
 /www.google.com/maps/dir//Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+9800+County+Hwy+M+B\
 ,+Bristol\,+WI+53104/@42.5325263\,-88.0106238\,15z/data=!4m8!4m7!1m0!1m5!1
 m1!1s0x880f8801a9785563:0x7c0f952d2deb0125!2m2!1d-88.0106238!2d42.5325263\
 n\nTake I-94 North. A few miles past the Wisconsin border take Exit #347 H
 wy 165/Cty Q. Turn left (west) at the end of the exit ramp. Go west 2.5 mi
 les on Cty Q. Turn right (north) on Cty MB for 0.8 miles. Turn left into t
 he Bristol Woods park entrance. Follow the park road about 1/4 mile past t
 he picnic shelter at the top of the hill to the Pringle Nature Center.\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods Park\, WI
CATEGORIES:.Fast Plus (17-19 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
