UID:TU2051905452
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Burlington\, WI (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Fast\n\nDistance: 60 Miles\
 n\nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n**!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Burlin
 gtonWI-2.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ride
 withgps.com/routes/43633474FAST group (15-17mph) leaving Bristol Woods at 
 09:00AM.**  \nRemote Start :Bristol_Woods_County_Park: https://maps.google
 .com/maps?q=Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+Bristol\,+WI&hl=en&sll=39.739318\,
 -89.266507&sspn=15.139708\,33.815918&oq=brist&hq=Bristol+Woods+County+Park
 \,+Bristol\,+WI&t=m&z=15.Take I-94 North. A few miles past the Wisconsin b
 order\, take Exit #347 Hwy 165/Cty Q. Turn left (west) at the end of the e
 xit ramp and go west 2.5 miles on Qty Q. Turn right (north) at Cty MB and 
 go 0.5 miles. Turn left into the park entrance. Park at the Pringle Nature
  Center - follow the park road about 1/4 mile past the picnic shelter at t
 he top of the hill. Allow an hour from Evanston.  \nThere will be some rol
 ling hills and maybe a few not so rolling. Most of the route is on scenic 
 rural roads. Lunch will be at a lovely cafe in Burlington - The Coffee Hou
 se at Chestnut &amp\; Pine. We will also stop for root beer floats at the 
 Dairy Queen in Silver Lake.\n\n*If weather is questionable check the Rides
  Forum after 7:30 AM.*\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods County Park\, WI
CATEGORIES:.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
