BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1315677942
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Burlington\, WI (Dennis Miller)
DESCRIPTION:Status: CHANGES PENDING!\n\nPace: Fast\n\nDistance: 60 Miles\n\
 nLeader: Dennis Miller\n\n**!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/BurlingtonWI-
 2.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewithgps
 .com/routes/43633474Dennis will lead the FAST group (15-17mph) leaving Bri
 stol Woods at 09:00AM.**  \nRemote Start :Bristol_Woods_County_Park: https
 ://maps.google.com/maps?q=Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+Bristol\,+WI&hl=en&s
 ll=39.739318\,-89.266507&sspn=15.139708\,33.815918&oq=brist&hq=Bristol+Woo
 ds+County+Park\,+Bristol\,+WI&t=m&z=15.Take I-94 North. A few miles past t
 he Wisconsin border\, take Exit #347 Hwy 165/Cty Q. Turn left (west) at th
 e end of the exit ramp and go west 2.5 miles on Qty Q. Turn right (north) 
 at Cty MB and go 0.5 miles. Turn left into the park entrance. Park at the 
 Pringle Nature Center - follow the park road about 1/4 mile past the picni
 c shelter at the top of the hill. Allow an hour from Evanston.  \nThere wi
 ll be some rolling hills and maybe a few not so rolling. Most of the route
  is on scenic rural roads. Lunch will be at a lovely cafe in Burlington - 
 The Coffee House at Chestnut &amp\; Pine. We will also stop for root beer 
 floats at the Dairy Queen in Silver Lake.\n\n*If weather is questionable c
 heck the Rides Forum after 7:30 AM.*\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods County Park\, WI
CATEGORIES:.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
