BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1425949924
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Burlington\, WI (Jay Twery)
DESCRIPTION:Status: CHANGES PENDING!\n\nPace: Fast Plus\n\nDistance: 56 Mil
 es\n\nLeader: Jay Twery\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.pn
 g: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/40014510\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images
 /cal/WisconsinBiking.jpgThis ride will be on quiet rural roads with little
  traffic and some steep hilly sections\, but mostly rollers. This ride is 
 surprisinglyscenic given it's only about an hour's drive from Evanston. Th
 ere will be a lunch stop at the Coffee Shop in Burlington\, and short brea
 k at miles 20 and 45. if you plan on coming along on the ride or have any 
 question please email Jay Twery @ jaytwery@gmail.com\n\nIf the weather doe
 sn't cooperate Jay will post a cancellation on the Rides Forum by 7:30 on 
 the day of the ride.\n\n**Directions to the start:**\n\nhttps://www.google
 .com/maps/dir//Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+9800+County+Hwy+M+B\,+Bristol\,
 +WI+53104/@42.5325263\,-88.0106238\,15z/data=!4m8!4m7!1m0!1m5!1m1!1s0x880f
 8801a9785563:0x7c0f952d2deb0125!2m2!1d-88.0106238!2d42.5325263\n\nTake I-9
 4 North. A few miles past the Wisconsin border take Exit #347 Hwy 165/Cty 
 Q. Turn left (west) at the end of the exit ramp. Go west 2.5 miles on Cty 
 Q. Turn right (north) on Cty MB for 0.8 miles. Turn left into the Bristol 
 Woods park entrance. Follow the park road about 1/4 mile past the picnic s
 helter at the top of the hill to the Pringle Nature Center.\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods Park\, WI
CATEGORIES:.Fast Plus (17-19 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20270703T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20270703T090000
CREATED:20230218T010539Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T232411Z
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY;BYMONTH=7;BYDAY=1SA
X-TEAMUP-STATUS:CHANGES PENDING!
X-TEAMUP-PACE:Fast Plus
X-TEAMUP-DISTANCE:56 Miles
X-TEAMUP-START-LOCATION:Bristol Woods Park\, WI
X-TEAMUP-LEADER:Jay Twery
