BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1680435219
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:G.O.A.T.S. Ride the Ups and Downs (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Any\n\nDistance: 32\, 52 or
  63 Miles\n\nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/ca
 l/G.O.A.T.S%20Cycling.jpgMeet at Start @ 8am. Our friends in Galena The G.
 O.A.T.S. (Go Out and Tour Somewhere) Bicycle Club - invite EBC members to 
 join them for their first challenging ride of the season: Ride the Ups and
  Downs. Enjoy a full day tour of beautiful Galena Country featuring specta
 cular views and a few hills (well maybe more than a few). This is a beauti
 ful ride with good challenges and an appropriate number of rest stops. Che
 ck the ride out at \\[Visitgalena.org\\]. The fee is $45 for the ride. For
  complete information on the ride please click on this link: https://www.b
 ikereg.com/ride-the-ups-and-downs. There are three routes - 32\, 52 and 63
  miles. Start is at CTE Academy 950_US_Rte_20_W\,_Elizabeth\,_IL_61028: ht
 tp://maps.google.com/?daddr=42.3136692\,-90.2374373. ***Peter Glaser*** wi
 ll be leading an EBC group on the 52 mile route at Fast Pace (15-17mph) bu
 t if you want to ride a different distance or at a different pace this rid
 e accommodates riders on whatever route and speed they choose.\n\n  Date:*
 * Saturday\, May 2\, 2026  \n *Rain or shine!**\\****  \n**Registration Fe
 e:** $45 in advance includes GOATS socks  \n $45 day of event no socks  \n
  **Fee Includes:** Map &amp\; cue sheets  \n Marked routes  \n SAG support
  (ends at 3pm)  \n Food &amp\; drink at rest stops\n\n## Routes: *32_Miles
 _(50_km)*: https://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/356472327 *52_Miles_(84_k
 m)*: https://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/362537913 *63_Miles_(100_km)*: 
 https://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/356500653\n\nhttps://www.bikereg.com
 /ride-the-ups-and-downs\n\n
LOCATION:Jo Daviess Carroll CTE Academy\, 950 US Rte 20 W\, Elizabeth\, IL 
  61028
CATEGORIES:...Any
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
