 ader: Vicki Zickenheiner\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/FoxRiverTrail
 .jpgJoin Vicki Zickenheiner on a scenic 25 mile ride along the Fox River T
 rail. We will ride at the low end of moderate. We will meet at Towne Park 
 in Algonquin. The parking lot is just past St Johns Lutheran School. Pull 
 all the way around in the parking lot to park near the restrooms. We will 
 stop at Al’s Cafe in Elgin for lunch. Closer to the end of our ride we c
 an stop at Dairy Queen or Vans Custard for a sweet treat. Please let me kn
 ow if you are coming\, so I can look for you. Call if you have any questio
 ns. Looking forward to the ride! Vicki Zickenheiner\, cell\, 773-505-6121.
 \n\n
LOCATION:Towne Park\, Algonquin\, IL
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
