UID:TU2023025272
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Intro to NW Indiana - "The Gritty and the Pretty" (Len Krietz)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 38 miles\n\nLe
 ader: Len Krietz\n\n# **Intro to NW Indiana - "The Gritty and the Pretty"*
 *\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Wolf%20Lake.jpg!https://ebcrides.org
 /images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/52106286This r
 ide is meant to introduce or reintroduce riders to cycling in "the industr
 ial underbelly of Chicago". While we will travel through some industrial a
 reas we will also ride city streets and neighborhoods in the close-in citi
 es of Hammond\, Whiting\, and Highland and as a bonus travel though the so
 uthernmost (and least accessible) Chicago neighborhood of Hegewisch. We wi
 ll also ride on and get a sampling of a few of the excellent Northwest Ind
 ian bike paths.\n\n## Some of the ride points of interest include:\n\nWhih
 ala Beach Park in Whiting\, the BP Refinery\, Marktown (a Progressive-era 
 planned worker community)\, the NW Indiana Welcome Center (with its salute
  to hometown son Jean Shepherd (whose stories were the basis of "A Christm
 as Story") \, and the Power's State Rec. Area at Wolf Lake. Our lunch stop
  will be the 18th St. Brewery in Hammond.\n\nContact Ride Leader with any 
 questions. Len Krietz: 773 251-6934 lkrietz2@gmail.com\n\n
LOCATION:The PAV  (Pavillion at Wolf Lake Memorial Park)\,  2324 Calumet A
 ve\, Hammond\, IN 46320
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
