UID:TU2023025274
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Visit to Ft Sheridan (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 30 Mi
 les\n\nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n# !https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Ft
 %20Sheridan%20Cavalry%20Training.jpgWe will visit a few interesting locati
 ons inside Fort Sheridan\n\n1\\. There was an airfield at the fort used du
 ring WWII. We will visit its location on the ride.\n\n2\\. Anti-aircraft t
 raining included firing at drones over the lake. The anti-aircraft gun on 
 display was actually designed and manufactured in Sweden.\n\n3\\. Training
  for the mounted Cavalry was a major activity at the fort until WWII. We w
 ill circle the "stable park" shown on the google map. Attached is a horsem
 anship photo from one of the displays. I found it both frightening and ent
 ertaining.\n\n4\\. There is a private home on the lake. It has a private r
 oad with electric gates.\n\n  \nLunch will be at Once Upon a Bagel in down
 town Highland Park. We will often ride paths rather than roads within the 
 fort to get a different view. The pace will be on the low side of moderate
 . Part of the ride will be along the lakefront in the Southeast corner of 
 the fort. We will have to walk our bikes over a short grass path.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
