SUMMARY:Ride of Silence (David Barish)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Casual\n\nDistance: 10 Miles\n\nLead
 er: David Barish\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: http
 s://ridewithgps.com/routes/13719785\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/ri
 de%20of%20silence.jpgEvanston will again participate in the International 
 Ride of Silence [](http://www.rideofsilence.org)http://www.rideofsilence.o
 rg. On this date riders all over the world will ride in silence to remembe
 r riders who have been injured or killed on the roads and to support cycli
 sts and cycling. **Starts at: Wheel &amp\; Sprocket 1027 Davis Evanston.**
  Please be at Wheel and Sprocket before 7pm so we can all talk before we s
 ilently leave on the 11 mile ride. Wheel and Sprocket will host us for som
 e refreshments after the ride. If you are riding home you will need a ligh
 t as it will be dark by the time we are done. Need a light? You can get on
 e at the shop. Rides all over the world leave at 7pm to honor and remember
  people injured or killed on the road. There is a listing for the ride at 
 Ride_of_Silence-_Evanston: http://www.thechainlink.org/events/ride-of-sile
 nce-evanston-2. Come ride with us. This will be at a very casual pace.If y
 ou want to ride but are not near Evanston at 7pm you can try one of the ot
 her Rides of Silence in the Chicago area. They are also listed on the cale
 ndar on The Chainlink.\n\n
LOCATION:Wheel & Sprocket\, Evanston
CATEGORIES:..Casual (10-12 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
