BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2023025280
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Apple Cider Century (Robert Slaughter)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Fast\, Any\n\nDistance: 15 - 100 mil
 es\n\nLeader: Robert Slaughter\n\n# **!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/App
 le%20Cider%20Century.jpgAPPLE CIDER CENTURY**\n\nOne of the largest and lo
 ngest running cycling events in the Midwest! Join the annual\, one-day bic
 ycle tour held on the last Sunday of September\, riding through orchards\,
  forests\, and wine country in and around Three Oaks\, Michigan. Cyclists 
 choose from routes of 15\, 25\, 37\, 50\, 62\, 75\, or 100 miles\, making 
 it accessible for riders of all ages and skill levels. **Bob will lead a f
 ast group on the 100 mile route** but riders choose whatever pace and dist
 ance they wish.\n\n**The Apple Cider Century (ACC) takes place in the** **
 Village_of_Three_Oaks**: https://www.google.com/maps/place/Three+Oaks\,+MI
 +49128**\, located about 60 miles from both Chicago and Kalamazoo. Started
  in 1974\, the event has grown into one of the Midwest's largest century e
 vents\, drawing up to 4\,000 participants each year.** Run and organized b
 y the Three_Oaks_Spokes_Bicycle_Club: https://www.applecidercentury.com/th
 ree-oaks-spokes.\n\n​The weekend of the ride offers a wide range of acti
 vities\, including vendor stalls\, **Ice Cream Social on Saturday**\, live
  music\, a tasty spaghetti dinner and the all-you-can-eat breakfast for pu
 rchase\, provided by the Three Oaks Fire Department. And of course\, there
 's an abundance of cider and apples to enjoy!\n\n​If you're looking for 
 more to do in the area\, start by visiting the Dewey Cannon Trading Compan
 y &amp\; Bicycle Museum. Here you will find information on local events\, 
 winery tours\, antiques\, and shopping. The Bicycle Museum is home to uniq
 ue bicycles like the 1860's Boneshaker\, 1890's Tally-Ho Tandem\, Side-by-
 Side Tandem\, and various other historic cycling items. Don't forget to ex
 plore the gift shop! Entertainment in town includes the Vickers Theater fo
 r movies\, the Acorn_Theater: https://acornlive.org/ for live performances
 \, places for food &amp\; drink and several art galleries.\n\n**RSVP to ri
 de leader via email is appreciated:** Bob Slaughter r.z.slaughter@gmail.co
 m\n\n
LOCATION:St. Mary of the Assumption Church\, 28 W Ash St\, Three Oaks\, MI 
 49128
CATEGORIES:...Any,.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260927T070000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260927T070000
