BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2023025288
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Roger’s Park Bungalow Tour (David Barish)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Casual\n\nLeader: David Barish\n\n##
  A Casual tour of Roger’s Park bungalows\n\nJoin us on this tour through
  the Rogers Park Manor and Talman West Ridge Historic Bungalow Districts. 
 Built between 1915 and 1930 these two districts reflect the coming of age 
 of the Chicago bungalow. We will ride by many different homes built when l
 ocal architects and builders began experimenting with form and stylistic d
 etailing to create bungalows that were unique to Chicago. The ride will be
  at a relaxing pace where we will visit homes of notable Chicagoans from m
 ob bosses to Cubs catchers.\n\nThis ride will be co-led by Charlie Saxe fr
 om the Skokie Bike Betwork. It will start from the Cultural Center at Lunt
  &amp\; Campbell in Chicago in the Indian Boundary Park.\n\n
LOCATION:Indian Boundary Park Cultural Center\, Lunt & Campbell\, Chicago\,
  IL
CATEGORIES:..Casual (10-12 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
