SUMMARY:Tuesday Moderate: Hilly North Shore (Neal Ney)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 36 miles\n\nLe
 ader: Neal Ney\n\n**!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/HILLS!.jpg!https://eb
 crides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/4590
 0018This week's Tuesday Moderate Ride:** One of the best ways to improve o
 ne’s cycling is through hill training. This route seeks out the "hills" 
 on the North Shore. Many will be familiar to Tuesday moderate riders\, but
  others are lesser-known lakefront access roads. Some are easily bypassed 
 if you really don’t want to do all of the hills. A single ride with lots
  of climbs will not elevate your cycling a great deal\, but the point of t
 he ride is to give everyone the information about where the hills are if y
 ou ever want to give hill training a try. A number of lunch locations are 
 available just slightly off the route\, and our lunch location(s) will be 
 selected on the day of the ride\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
