BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2023025299
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Garrison Site in Lake Forest (Neal Ney)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 40 miles\n\nLe
 ader: Neal Ney\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Garrison%20Site%20Plaqu
 e.jpg  \n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewit
 hgps.com/routes/36054459 A ride to an important but little known archeolog
 ical site. It is marked today by only a simple plaque on a bolder\, but it
  is neat to know that there were human settlements 10\,000 years ago in th
 e midst of the communities we regularly ride through.\n\nThe Garrison Site
  is an archaeological site in Lake Forest that was excavated in 1991-1992.
  It is located north of Westleigh Road near Wallace Road and the Carroll M
 eadow Nature Preserve and was excavated when a new road was put in by deve
 loper Barry Carroll.\n\nThe Garrison site yielded some of the oldest and b
 est documented evidence of human occupation in Northeast Illinois. Archaeo
 logical evidence from the site shows that Paleo Indians were present in La
 ke Forest as long as 10\,000 years ago\, though most items found date to t
 he Woodland Period. The site was named in honor of the late Morrow Garriso
 n who had worked closely with Barry Carroll on various developments.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260616T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260616T090000
CREATED:20260112T230618Z
