 ver quiet secondary roads with SAG support. No pre-registration available-
  only same day registration for $15.\n\nThis is an enjoyable ride. And tou
 gh to beat a ride that features tasty baked goods and a scenic route for j
 ust a $15 day-of-ride fee with no pre-registration required.  \nWe meet at
  Wauconda High School at 8:50 am (with the intent of getting into the regi
 stration line before 9 am groups.show up). We will do both loops (38 miles
 ) plus our own extension (8.5 miles) for a total around 47 miles.\n\n  \nH
 ere is link to the ride page with location and directions: https://www.whe
 elmen.com/st\\_pats.asp: https://www.wheelmen.com/st_pats.asp  \n  \nAnd h
 ere is a route map that includes both the 17 and 21 mile loops: https://ri
 dewithgps.com/trips/85228489  \n  \n8.5 mile extension (38 miles seems a b
 it short to justify the drive to Wauconda. If anyone knows the area\, plea
 se feel free to come up with a better extension route): https://ridewithgp
 s.com/routes/42140472\n\n
