BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2023025341
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Burlington\, WI (Ride Leader Needed)
DESCRIPTION:Status: RIDE LEADER NEEDED\n\nPace: Fast Plus\n\nDistance: 60 M
 iles\n\nLeader: Ride Leader Needed\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWG
 PS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/43633474\n\n!https://ebcrides
 .org/images/cal/WisconsinBiking.jpgThis is a 60-mile ride\, starting at Br
 istol Woods County Park in Wisconsin\, at the low end of Fast Plus\, on on
 e of our favorite routes.\n\nThere will be some rolling hills and maybe a 
 few not-so-rolling. Most of the route is on scenic rural roads. Lunch will
  be in Burlington at The Coffee House at Chestnut &amp\; Pine. We will als
 o stop briefly at the Dairy Queen in Silver Lake on our way back. Return t
 o Bristol Woods roughly 3:00 pm.\n\nTo avoid a potentially long line at Th
 e Coffee House\, you can order and pay ahead online: http://www.burlington
 coffeehouse.com/menu. (If you do this\, specify 11:15 am as the pickup tim
 e for your order.)\n\nAfter the ride\, we may adjourn to the biergarten at
  Petrifying Springs Park for beverages and snacks. It’s about a 20-minut
 e drive from our start location. More information here: https://www.travel
 wisconsin.com/pubs-taverns/petrifying-springs-biergarten-307249\n\n**Direc
 tions to start**: Take I-94 North. A few miles past the Wisconsin border\,
  take Exit #347 Hwy 165/Cty Q. Turn left (west) at the end of the exit ram
 p. Go west 2.5 miles on Cty Q. Turn right (north) on Cty MB for 0.8 miles.
  Turn left into the Bristol Woods park entrance. Follow the park road abou
 t 1/4 mile past the picnic shelter at the top of the hill to the Pringle N
 ature Center.\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods Park\, WI
CATEGORIES:.Fast Plus (17-19 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
