UID:TU2023025350
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Arlington 500 Ride ($) (Scott Schaedel)
DESCRIPTION:Status: PENDING!\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 41 Miles\n\nLea
 der: Scott Schaedel\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/AHBC%20Arlington%2
 05000.jpgThe Arlington 500 is a recreational bike ride on scenic roads in 
 Lake County\, Illinois. The Arlington Heights Bicycle Club (AHBC) has host
 ed this ride for over 40 years. This ride is similar to the NSC in that ri
 ders can choose their  \nown pace and distance of a 20\, 41\, 66\, 87\, or
  101 mile route. RWGPS  \nroutes and print cue sheets can be downloaded. T
 here will also be  \nsignage road markers.\n\nRest stop with wide variety 
 of food and beverages until 3:00PM.  \nSupport vehicles on the route until
  3:30PM.  \nMostly level terrain with some moderate hills.\n\nWe will meet
  as a group beforehand and self-sort into pace and distance groups.\n\n**S
 tart: Lake Zurich High School\, 300 Church Street\, Lake Zurich\, IL 60047
 .**\n\nDetails and sign-up are available on the Arlington Heights Bicycle 
 Club website:\n\nhttps://cyclearlington.com/AHBC-500/Arlington-500.html\n\
 nRWGPS routes can be found at  \nhttps://cyclearlington.com/AHBC-500/Arlin
 gton-500-Route.html\n\nNote that the routes (A through E) are additive (i.
 e.\, all start and end at the starting location). To ride your desired dis
 tance\, you will download multiple loops building up to your desired ride.
 \n\n**Please RSVP Scott Schaedel at svschaed2@gmail.com if you are plannin
 g to ride.**\n\n
LOCATION:Lake Zurich High School\, 300 Church Street\, Lake Zurich\, IL 600
 47
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
