BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2023025353
DTSTAMP:20260317T225617Z
SUMMARY:Grand Illinois Bike Tour (Sharon Kaminecki)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\, Any\n\nDistance: 203-400 
 miles (47-58 daily)\n\nLeader: Sharon Kaminecki\n\n***!https://ebcrides.or
 g/images/cal/Grand%20Illinois%20Bike%20Tour%202020.jpg***!https://ebcrides
 .org/images/cal/GIBT%202024.jpg\n\n## **Annual Grand Illinois Bike Tour (G
 IBT)**\n\nThis year’s route explores North Central Illinois beginning an
 d ending in Rochelle\, with overnights in pre-reserved hotels in Ottawa\, 
 DeKalb and Rockford. Choose among daily mileage options for a total betwee
 n 200 to 375 miles\, consisting mainly of quiet rural roads and trails. Pr
 oceeds benefit GIBT’s host Ride Illinois\, a nonprofit bicycle advocacy 
 organization\, and supports their mission to make Illinois better through 
 biking. More information and registration: https://rideillinois.org/events
 /2025-grand-illinois-bike-tour/\n\nOur loop through Central Illinois will 
 first make its way to Springfield\, the state capitol and home of many Abr
 aham Lincoln historical sites. Day two’s layover day provides an opportu
 nity to tour those sites and the extensive Springfield area paved trail sy
 stem. We then continue our figure eight formation for a night in Forsyth. 
 From there it is off to the home of the University of Illinois Fighting Il
 lini\, with two nights in Champaign and layover day routes in the area. Th
 is year’s ride concludes on rural roads to Maroa. Join us and invite you
 r friends.\n\nChoose among our daily mileage options for a total between 2
 03-400 miles\, consisting mainly of quiet rural roads as well as some pave
 d trails around Kewanee\, the Quad Cities\, following the Mississippi Rive
 r to Savanna and then to Rock Falls. Pick between our hotel and our modifi
 ed\, semi-independent (details below) group camping options. \\[Note: We d
 o still have space for our semi-independent camping option with informatio
 n on how to register in that section below.\\] Enjoy evenings filled with 
 good food and socializing with riders from around the country. Proceeds be
 nefit Ride_Illinois: https://rideillinois.org/\, a nonprofit bicycle advoc
 acy organization\, and support our mission to make Illinois better through
  biking.\n\n**Our fully supported tour basics:**\n\n- Daily route distance
 s between 47 to 58 miles. Longer route and layover day options are availab
 le. RideWithGPS: https://ridewithgps.com/ and cue sheets will be provided 
 for navigation. (Find more information in “Route\, Mileage\, and Navigat
 ion” below.)\n- SAG (pickup) support\, refreshment and water stops\, and
  t-shirt are included. Local bike shops will be providing expert bike repa
 ir. (See “Extra third-party services” below for other offerings includ
 ing camping rentals and set-up services\, as well as massage service.)\n- 
 Hotelers get luggage transportation\, hotel breakfasts and two catered din
 ners\, and evening receptions. (Three dinners will be “on-your-own” at
  nearby or adjacent restaurants.)\n- A semi-independent group camping opti
 on (different from past years\, see below) at state and county campgrounds
  and a city park includes two catered dinners at the hotels.\n- Important 
 updates during GIBT will be sent via email (with printouts for those witho
 ut smartphones) or text\, when necessary.\n- Join the fun after dinner\, a
 s fellow riders play music and invite you to sing along.\n- Velosophie\, a
 n optional reading discussion group\, meets before dinner each day.\n\n**T
 he ride is limited to 130 hotelers and 190 total riders.**\n\nSharon will 
 be leading a group at Moderate (13-15 mph) pace but riders can choose what
 ever pace and distance they prefer and report their daily mileage. Please 
 let Sharon know if you plan to join this ride so she can look for you: kam
 inecki@aol.com\n\n**Meet at 8:30 am at the start: Maroa Forsyth High Schoo
 l\, 610 West Washington St.\, Maroa\, IL 61756**\n\n
LOCATION:Maroa Forsyth High School\, 610 West Washington St.\, Maroa\, IL 6
 1756
CATEGORIES:...Any,..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
